news.title: What real estate industry gained in Budget 2025?
news.para: With a strong emphasis on urban infrastructure, housing, and investment, the budget 2025 brings several key measures impacting the real estate sector.

news.title: Over 250 projects register with Uttar Pradesh RERA in 2024
news.para: Among the major cities, Lucknow recorded 61 project registrations with UP-RERA and is expected to witness the construction of nearly 54,000 homes, while Gautam Buddh Nagar saw 51 new projects and will see over 1.1 lakh new homes coming up.

news.title: MMMRDA introduces online system to streamline development permissions in Mumbai
news.para: This digital platform will be implemented in key areas, including Bandra Kurla Complex, Oshiwara District Centre, Wadala Notified Area, and CSMI Airport Notified Area, as part of efforts to modernise urban development processes.

news.title: Karnataka approves plan to develop satellite towns near Bengaluru
news.para: Law and Parliamentary Affairs Minister HK Patil said, “Under the Greater Bengaluru Development Authority (GBDA), the Ramnagar district including areas like Bidadi Hobli, Byramangala, Bannigiri, Hosur, Kempaiah Palya, and Harohalli Hobli, will be developed as part of the “Greater Bengaluru Suburban Project.”

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to auction 608 properties in eight zones
news.para: The 608 properties include 118 in east zone, 120 in west, 109 in south, 60 in Mahadevapura, 70 in Bommanahalli, 40 in Yelahanka, 50 in RR Nagar and 41 in Dasarahalli. BBMP officials said tax dues from these properties add to nearly Rs 20 crore.

news.title: Door-to-door drive for verification of property IDs in Haryana soon
news.para: The administration and civic bodies of the districts have been directed to first fix the issues related to property before streamlining the collection of property tax.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government notifies urban planning and development rules
news.para: The permit fees would have to be paid at the time of submitting the initial layout plan of a project. The housing department would collect fees from private developers and colonisers based on the total area of the layout plan.

news.title: Bombay HC raps BMC and SRA for constructions on plot reserved for playground
news.para: "No construction activity can be permitted in respect of the area which is earmarked for a playground," said Chief Justice Alok Aradhe and Justice Bharati Dangre while hearing a PIL by three local residents — Dileep Saptarshi, Robert Wiesinger and Sunil Bhatia.

news.title: Over 250 contractors of Supertech approach NCLAT over Rs 200 crore dues
news.para: On Thursday, the contractors' application challenged both the IRP's conduct and the NCLAT's Dec 12, 2024, order, which appointed state-owned NBCC to complete 16 delayed Supertech housing projects.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace Developers posts net loss of Rs 22.47 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 185.77 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 109.27 per cent from Rs 88.77 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's net profit up 22.75% in Q3 FY25
news.para: LIC Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 7,069.99 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 3.91 per cent from Rs 6,804.19 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 90.42 lakh assets in Rs 10 crore real estate fraud case in Lucknow
news.para: The attached assets include 0.082 hectares of agricultural land located in Rahmatnagar village, Mohanlalganj, Lucknow, registered in the name of the company.

news.title: Resolve all complaints of residents in a week: NMC commissioner
news.para: Taking serious cognizance of this, municipal commissioner Manisha Khatri instructed the officials concerned to immediately address the grievances and resolve all the pending issues within a week.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body approves budget of Rs 8,440 crore for 2025-26
news.para: The budget was approved during the GHMC council meeting, presided over by Mayor Vijaya Lakshmi R Gadwal.

news.title: Goa government forms panel to revise circle rates of properties
news.para: The committee will analyse the current market trends and rates and propose a revised circle rate for land. It is also tasked to suggest a mechanism to periodically revise the rates as well as ways to improve the revenue mobilisation.

news.title: Lodha brothers agree to go for mediation to resolve dispute over 'Lodha' trademark
news.para: After the HC suggested to both parties earlier this week to attempt an amicable resolution, the brothers on Friday told a single bench of Justice Arif Doctor they were willing to go for mediation.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh govt initiates land acquisition for metro projects in Vijayawada, Vizag
news.para: Speaking to TOI, NTR district collector Dr G Lakshimisha said, "We received the govt orders to acquire a total of 91.69 acres for the construction of a metro spanning 38.4 km along Penamaluru and Gannavaram corridors as part of the Vijayawada metro rail project."

news.title: Nashik: Over 1,000 building plans await approval from town planning department
news.para: Municipal commissioner Manisha Khatri, in order to streamline the building plan proposal submission and spped up the approval process, made the online process mandatory and discontinued the offline system.

news.title: Budget 2025: Private investment needs a boost, real estate sector can be the catalyst
news.para: ​Simplification of input tax credit mechanism will help lowering down the cost of construction and will help in development of investible grade assets, which can be lucrative to the private equity sector.

news.title: SRG Housing Finance's net profit up 7.89% in Q3 FY25
news.para: SRG Housing Finance's net total income stood at Rs 40.25 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 24.96 per cent from Rs 32.21 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
